                        <handDesc>  
                            <handNote scope="sole" xml:id="hand-1">
                                <locus from="1r" to="5v">ff. 1r-5v </locus>
                                Hand A: the text has been written by a hand datable to the 17th c., a small informal minuscule, 
                                slightly slanting to the right, characterized by ornamental hooks at the end of uprights. 
                                The same hand is found on MSS Add. 1880.13 (hand A), and 1880.16 (identification already proposed by 
                                R.V. Kerr in an unpublished description kept in Cambridge University Library).
                            </handNote>
                        </handDesc>
                        
                        <decoDesc>
                            <decoNote type="diagrams"> A few very simple diagrams in red ink by the scribe accompany the text on 
                                ff. <locus from="1r" to="1r"> 1r</locus> and <locus from="3v" to="3v"> 3v</locus>.</decoNote>
                        </decoDesc>
                        
                        <additions> 
